title: Saysomething
position: 17,-32
---
TaxiDriver: Uhm... I-I'm gonna change channels
Narrator: While looking at the road you search the channel knob with your right hand. You think you have found it ,but your mussle memory is telling you otherwise, it's a knob, yes, but it dosen't feel like the car radio one. You turn it anyways
Narrator: (There is a bit of silence for a few seconds, silence broken by a bit of static, until...)
Taxi: Hey man, Is that you? Did you get the girl? Hello? Oh by the way you still owe me 20 dolars from yesterday just as a reminder...
Narrator: Turns out your musle memory wasn't lying, that was not the car radio knob, that was the taxi radio one. Now your co-worker is talking. Fuck, I close my eyes for a bit and i breath. I can see her eyes light up for a second and she is smiling. Way to go man
NarratorG: But  can you blame me? It's just a funny situation no the end of the world. I can see him visibly upset, I won't say anything just yet, I don't want to make him more nervous than he already is.
TaxiDriver: -Um H-Hi yeah I got her. We are heading there right now. 
Taxi: Right now? You are still not there yet? Man poor girl, she must be dying to get there, you better get there in time man or else I'm gonna up those 20 dolars you owe me to 40.
Narrator:I want to be anywhere but in this taxi right now
Pasajera:I want to say mr radio man that your friend here is doing a fantastic job of getting me to my destination and you shouldn't worry about a thing.
Taxi:If you say so... I guess you will just be owing me 20, lucky you. Anyways i'll leave you to it man see ya.
Narrator:As soon as you get the oportunity you turn off the taxi radio, leaving just the sound of the engine and the road 
Pasajera: Was that your friend?
TaxiDriver:Y-Yeah
Pasajera:He sounds nice.
TaxiDriver:(Sigh)- Yeah he is.
<<jump Silence>>
